props(properties)
*props are data passed from parent component to child component 

Without props:

function User() {
  return <h1>Ithesh</h1>;
}

Always shows:

Ithesh


with properties we can display same component different data 

With props:

<User name="Ithesh" />
<User name="Rahul" />
<User name="Priya" />

Now same component displays different data.


react properties we can easly rember like taking example of instagram  in insatgram for all user profile layout is same(same,logo,same color everything ) but only data changes 

. Why Do We Need Props?

Imagine Instagram.

Every profile page uses the same layout:

Profile Photo
Name
Bio
Followers

But data changes.

React solves this using props.

Instead of creating:

User1.jsx
User2.jsx
User3.jsx

We create:

User.jsx

And pass data through props.

