5. Line-by-Line Explanation

Example:

function User(props) {
  return <h1>{props.name}</h1>;
}
function

Creates a React component.

User

Component name.

Must start with capital letter.

props

An object containing passed data.

Example:

<User name="Ithesh" age="22" />

Props becomes:

{
  name: "Ithesh",
  age: "22"
}
props.name

Accesses name value.

props.name

returns:

"Ithesh"

<h1>{props.name}</h1>
