Modern Method: Destructuring Props

Instead of:

function User(props){
  return <h1>{props.name}</h1>;
}

Use:

function User({ name }) {
  return <h1>{name}</h1>;
}


Why?

Cleaner code.

Industry standard.

Example
function User({ name, age }) {
  return (
    <>
      <h1>{name}</h1>
      <p>{age}</p>
    </>
  );
}


9. Common Mistakes
Mistake 1
function user() {}

Wrong.

Component names must start with capital letter.

function User() {}

Correct.


Mistake 2
<h1>props.name</h1>

Wrong.

Output:

props.name

Correct:

<h1>{props.name}</h1>

Mistake 3
<User name=Ithesh />

Wrong.

Correct:

<User name="Ithesh" />


Mistake 4
function User(name){
}

Wrong.

React sends props object.

Correct:

function User(props){
}

or

function User({name}){
}


what is props(property)

props is data transformed from parent component to child component


Q2. Are Props Mutable?

No.

Props are read-only.

Never modify props directly.


